<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-10T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-10T10:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">831.24/479: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-10T11:00:00-04:00">March 10, 1943—11
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>169. Embassy’s 185 of February 16.<note n="6" xml:id="d283fn6">Not
                                    printed.</note> In the absence of any further advice, the Board
                                of Economic Warfare has announced in Current Export Bulletin No. 80,
                                dated March 5,<note n="8" xml:id="d283fn8">Issued by the Office of
                                    Exports of the Board of Economic Warfare.</note> that the
                                Decentralization plan<note n="9" xml:id="d283fn9">Decentralization
                                    Plan A; for an outline of this plan, see circular airgram of
                                    January 19, 8 p.m., <ref target="#pg_106">p. 106</ref>.</note>
                                will become effective April 1. Wire confirmation immediately.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>